# ============================================================================
# AI Dev Companion - Environment Variables
# ============================================================================

# REQUIRED: Anthropic API Key
# Get your API key at: https://console.anthropic.com/account/keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# OPTIONAL: Claude Model
# Available models:
# - claude-sonnet-4-20250514 (recommended, most capable)
# - claude-3-7-sonnet-20250219
# - claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022
# Default: claude-sonnet-4-20250514
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-20250514

# OPTIONAL: Allowed Commands
# Comma-separated list of commands that Claude can execute
# Default: npm,git,cat,ls,pwd,echo,npx,node
# ALLOWED_COMMANDS=npm,git,cat,ls,pwd,echo,npx,node

# OPTIONAL: Base URL
# Used for internal API calls. Change if deploying to production.
# Default: http://localhost:3000
# NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES:
# ============================================================================
# - NEVER commit this file with your actual API key
# - Add .env to .gitignore (already done)
# - Keep your API key secret
# - Rotate your key if it's exposed
#
# For more info: https://docs.anthropic.com/claude/reference/getting-started-with-the-api

# ============================================================================
# DOCKER CONFIGURATION (optional)
# ============================================================================

# Data directory for persistence
# DATA_DIR=/app/data

# Workspaces directory for cloned projects
# WORKSPACES_DIR=/app/workspaces

# ============================================================================
# MCP (Model Context Protocol) SERVERS (optional)
# ============================================================================
# MCP servers can be configured via the UI at /settings/mcp
# or by creating a mcp-servers.json file in the data directory
